The ratio refers to the available data rate in excess of the Minimum Data Rate, summed over all bearer channels. Also, the 100 - vdsl2ServProfCh2RaRatioUs is the ratio of excess data rate to be assigned to all other bearer channels on Upstream direction. The sum of rate adaptation ratios over all bearers on the same direction shall be equal to 100%. Unit: percents

vdsl2ServProfRowStatus.name: vdsl2ServProfRowStatus
vdsl2ServProfRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or to modify or delete an existing row in this table. A profile is activated by setting this object to 'active'. When 'active' is set, the system will validate the profile. Before a profile can be deleted or taken out of service (by setting this object to 'destroy' or 'outOfService'), it must be not referenced from all associated lines.

hwvdsl2ServProfMinEtrRtxDs.name: hwvdsl2ServProfMinEtrRtxDs
hwvdsl2ServProfMinEtrRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum expected throughput for the bearer channel.The values range in steps of 1000 bit/s.

hwvdsl2ServProfMinEtrRtxUs.name: hwvdsl2ServProfMinEtrRtxUs
hwvdsl2ServProfMinEtrRtxUs.description: If retransmission is used in upstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum expected throughput for the bearer channel.The values range in steps of 1000 bit/s.

hwvdsl2ServProfMaxEtrRtxDs.name: hwvdsl2ServProfMaxEtrRtxDs
hwvdsl2ServProfMaxEtrRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the maximum expected throughput for the bearer channel.The values range in steps of 1000 bit/s.

hwvdsl2ServProfMaxEtrRtxUs.name: hwvdsl2ServProfMaxEtrRtxUs
hwvdsl2ServProfMaxEtrRtxUs.description: If retransmission is used in upstream direction, this parameter specifies the maximum expected throughput for the bearer channel.The values range in steps of 1000 bit/s.

hwvdsl2ServProfMaxNdrRtxDs.name: hwvdsl2ServProfMaxNdrRtxDs
hwvdsl2ServProfMaxNdrRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the maximum net data rate for the bearer channel. The values range in steps of 1000 bit/s.

hwvdsl2ServProfMaxNdrRtxUs.name: hwvdsl2ServProfMaxNdrRtxUs
hwvdsl2ServProfMaxNdrRtxUs.description: If retransmission is used in upstream direction, this parameter specifies the maximum net data rate for the bearer channel.The values range in steps of 1000 bit/s.

vdsl2SpectrumProfTable.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfTable
vdsl2SpectrumProfTable.description: The table vdsl2SpectrumProfTable contains VDSL2 line spectrum configuration. The index of this table is vdsl2SpectrumProfName. A default profile with an index of 'DEFVAL' will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor-specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdsl2SpectrumProfEntry.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfEntry
vdsl2SpectrumProfEntry.description: The table vdsl2SpectrumProfTable contains VDSL2 line spectrum configuration. The index of this entry is vdsl2SpectrumProfName. A default profile with an index of 'DEFVAL' will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor-specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdsl2SpectrumProfName.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfName
vdsl2SpectrumProfName.description: This object identifies a row in this table.

vdsl2SpectrumProfXtuTransSysEna.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfXtuTransSysEna
vdsl2SpectrumProfXtuTransSysEna.description: xTU Transmission System Enabling (xTSE). A list of the different coding types enabled in this profile. It is coded in a bit-map representation with 1 or more bits set. A bit set to '1' means that the XTUs may apply the respective coding for the VDSL line. A bit set to '0' means that the XTUs cannot apply the respective coding for the VDSL line. All 'reserved' bits should be set to '0'.

vdsl2SpectrumProfScMaskDs.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfScMaskDs
vdsl2SpectrumProfScMaskDs.description: Sub-carriers mask. A bitmap of 512 bits that allows masking up to 512 downstream sub-carriers, depending on NSCds. If bit i (0 <= i < NSCds) is set to '1', the respective downstream sub-carrier i is masked, and if set to '0', the respective sub-carrier is unmasked. Note that there should always be unmasked sub-carriers (i.e., the object cannot be all 1's). Also note that if NSCds < 512, all bits i (NSCds i <= 512) should be set to '1'.

vdsl2SpectrumProfScMaskUs.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfScMaskUs
vdsl2SpectrumProfScMaskUs.description: Sub-carriers mask. A bitmap of 64 bits that allows masking up to 64 downstream sub-carriers, depending on NSCds. If bit i (0 <= i < NSCus) is set to '1', the respective upstream sub-carrier i is masked, and if set to '0', the respective sub-carrier is unmasked. Note that there should always be unmasked sub-carriers (i.e., the object cannot be all 1's). Also note that if NSCus < 64, all bits i (NSCus < i <= 64) should be set to '1'.

vdsl2SpectrumProfVDSLtoneblackout.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfVDSLtoneblackout
vdsl2SpectrumProfVDSLtoneblackout.description: The subset of subcarriermask that shall be used to mask the subcarriers. It is a string of bands consist of begin tone index and end tone index. for example :0-10,20-50,100-4095 It can contain as most as 8 bands.

vdsl2SpectrumProfRfiBands.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfRfiBands
vdsl2SpectrumProfRfiBands.description: The subset of PSD mask breakpoints that shall be used to notch an RFI band. It is a string of bands consist of begin tone index and end tone index. for example :0-10,20-50,100-4095 It can contain as most as 16 bands.

vdsl2SpectrumProfRowStatus.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfRowStatus
vdsl2SpectrumProfRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or to modify or delete an existing row in this table. A profile is activated by setting this object to 'active'. When 'active' is set, the system will validate the profile. Before a profile can be deleted or taken out of service (by setting this object to 'destroy' or 'outOfService'), it must be not referenced from all associated lines.

hwvdsl2SpectrumProfRtxModeDs.name: hwvdsl2SpectrumProfRtxModeDs
hwvdsl2SpectrumProfRtxModeDs.description: The mode of operation of G.998.4 retransmission in downstream direction. Options: 1. forbidden(0) - G.998.4 retransmission not allowed. 2. preferred(1) - G.998.4 retransmission is preferred. 3. forced(2) - Force the use of the G.998.4 retransmission. 4. testmode(3) - Force the use of the G.998.4 retransmission in test mode.

hwvdsl2SpectrumProfRtxModeUs.name: hwvdsl2SpectrumProfRtxModeUs
hwvdsl2SpectrumProfRtxModeUs.description: The mode of operation of G.998.4 retransmission in upstream direction. Options: 1. forbidden(0) - G.998.4 retransmission not allowed. 2. preferred(1) - G.998.4 retransmission is preferred. 3. forced(2) - Force the use of the G.998.4 retransmission. 4. testmode(3) - Force the use of the G.998.4 retransmission in test mode.

hwvdsl2SpectrumProfProfLeftrThreshDs.name: hwvdsl2SpectrumProfProfLeftrThreshDs
hwvdsl2SpectrumProfProfLeftrThreshDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the threshold for declaring a near-end leftr defect. The value is coded as a fraction of the NDR with valid range from 0.01 to 0.99 with increments of 0.01. A special value means the ETR shall be used as the default threshold for declaring a leftr defect.

hwvdsl2SpectrumProfProfLeftrThreshUs.name: hwvdsl2SpectrumProfProfLeftrThreshUs
hwvdsl2SpectrumProfProfLeftrThreshUs.description: If retransmission is used in upstream direction, this parameter specifies the threshold for declaring a near-end leftr defect. The value is coded as a fraction of the NDR with valid range from 0.01 to 0.99 with increments of 0.01. A special value means the ETR shall be used as the default threshold for declaring a leftr defect.

vdsl2SpectrumProfModeSpecTable.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfModeSpecTable
vdsl2SpectrumProfModeSpecTable.description: The table vdsl2SpectrumProfModeSpecTable extends the VDSL2 line configuration profile by VDSL Mode Specific parameters. A row in this table that has an index of vdsl2LconfProfVdslMode == defMode(1), is called a 'mandatory' row. A row in this table that has an index such that vdsl2LconfProfVdslMode is not equal to defMode(1), is called an 'optional' row. When a row in the vdsl2LineConfProfTable table (the parent row) is created, the SNMP agent will automatically create a 'mandatory' row in this table. When the parent row is deleted, the SNMP agent will automatically delete all associated rows in this table. Any attempt to delete the 'mandatory' row using the vdsl2LConfProfModeSpecRowStatus attribute will be rejected by the SNMP agent. The manager MAY create an 'optional' row in this table using the vdsl2LConfProfModeSpecRowStatus attribute if the parent row exists. The manager MAY delete an 'optional' row in this table using the vdsl2LConfProfModeSpecRowStatus attribute at any time. If the actual transmission mode of a DSL line does not match one of the 'optional' rows in this table, then the line will use the PSD configuration from the 'mandatory' row. The indexes of this table are vdsl2SpectrumProfName and vdsl2SpectrumProfXdslMode.

vdsl2SpectrumProfModeSpecEntry.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfModeSpecEntry
vdsl2SpectrumProfModeSpecEntry.description: The table vdsl2SpectrumProfModeSpecTable extends the VDSL2 line configuration profile by VDSL Mode Specific parameters. A row in this table that has an index of vdsl2LconfProfVdslMode == defMode(1), is called a 'mandatory' row. A row in this table that has an index such that vdsl2LconfProfVdslMode is not equal to defMode(1), is called an 'optional' row. When a row in the vdsl2LineConfProfTable table (the parent row) is created, the SNMP agent will automatically create a 'mandatory' row in this table. When the parent row is deleted, the SNMP agent will automatically delete all associated rows in this table. Any attempt to delete the 'mandatory' row using the vdsl2LConfProfModeSpecRowStatus attribute will be rejected by the SNMP agent. The manager MAY create an 'optional' row in this table using the vdsl2LConfProfModeSpecRowStatus attribute if the parent row exists. The manager MAY delete an 'optional' row in this table using the vdsl2LConfProfModeSpecRowStatus attribute at any time. If the actual transmission mode of a DSL line does not match one of the 'optional' rows in this table, then the line will use the PSD configuration from the 'mandatory' row. The indexes of this entry are vdsl2SpectrumProfName and vdsl2SpectrumProfXdslMode.

vdsl2SpectrumProfXdslMode.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfXdslMode
vdsl2SpectrumProfXdslMode.description: The xDSL Mode is a way of categorizing the various xDSL transmission modes into groups, each group (xDSL Mode) shares the same PSD configuration. There should be multiple entries in this table for a given line profile in case multiple bits are set in vdsl2LConfProfXtuTransSysEna for that profile.

vdsl2SpectrumProfMaxNomPsdDs.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfMaxNomPsdDs
vdsl2SpectrumProfMaxNomPsdDs.description: The maximum nominal transmit PSD in the downstream direction during initialization and Showtime. It ranges from -600 to -300 units of 0.1 dBm/Hz. (physical values are -60 to -30 dBm/Hz). Unit: 0.1 dBm/Hz

vdsl2SpectrumProfMaxNomPsdUs.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfMaxNomPsdUs
vdsl2SpectrumProfMaxNomPsdUs.description: The maximum nominal transmit PSD in the upstream direction during initialization and Showtime. It ranges from -600 to -300 units of 0.1 dBm/Hz. (physical values are -60 to -30 dBm/Hz). Unit: 0.1 dBm/Hz

vdsl2SpectrumProfMaxNomAtpDs.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfMaxNomAtpDs
vdsl2SpectrumProfMaxNomAtpDs.description: The maximum nominal aggregate transmit power in the downstream direction during initialization and Showtime. It ranges from 0 to 255 units of 0.1 dBm (physical values are 0 to 25.5 dBm). Unit: 0.1 dBm

vdsl2SpectrumProfMaxNomAtpUs.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfMaxNomAtpUs
vdsl2SpectrumProfMaxNomAtpUs.description: The maximum nominal aggregate transmit power in the upstream direction during initialization and Showtime. It ranges from 0 to 255 units of 0.1 dBm (physical values are 0 to 25.5 dBm). Unit: 0.1 dBm

vdsl2SpectrumProfMaxAggRxPwrUs.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfMaxAggRxPwrUs
vdsl2SpectrumProfMaxAggRxPwrUs.description: The maximum upstream aggregate receive power over the relevant set of sub-carriers. The xTU-C should verify that the upstream power cutback is such that this maximum aggregate receive power value is honored. It ranges from -255 to 255 units of 0.1 dBm (physical values are -25.5 to 25.5 dBm). A value of all means that there is no limit. Unit: 0.1 dBm

vdsl2SpectrumProfPsdMaskDs.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfPsdMaskDs
vdsl2SpectrumProfPsdMaskDs.description: This configuration parameter defines the downstream PSD mask applicable at the U-C2 reference point. This MIB PSD mask may impose PSD restrictions in addition to the Limit PSD mask defined in the relevant Recommendation (e.g., G.992.5, G.993.2). This is a string of 32 pairs of values in the following structure: Octets 0+1 - Index of 1st sub-carrier used in the context of a first breakpoint. Octet 2 - The PSD reduction for the sub-carrier indicated in octets 0 and 1. Octets 3-5 - Same, for a 2nd breakpoint. Octets 6-8 - Same, for a 3rd breakpoint. This architecture continues until octets 94-95, which are associated with a 32nd breakpoint. Each subcarrier index is an unsigned number in the range 0 and (NSCds - 1). Each PSD reduction value is in the range 0 (0dBm/Hz) to 255 (-127.5dBm/Hz) with steps of 0.5dBm/Hz. Valid values are in the range 0 to 190 (0 to -95dBm/Hz). When the number of breakpoints is less than 32, all remaining octets are set to the value 0xff. Note that the content of this object should be correlated with the sub-carriers mask and with the RFI setup.

vdsl2SpectrumProfPsdMaskUs.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfPsdMaskUs
vdsl2SpectrumProfPsdMaskUs.description: This configuration parameter defines the upstream PSD mask applicable at the U R2 reference point. This MIB PSD mask may impose PSD restrictions in addition to the Limit PSD mask defined in the relevant Recommendations (e.g., ITU-T Recommendations G.992.3, G.993.2). This is a string of 16 pairs of values in the following structure: Octets 0+1 - Index of 1st sub-carrier used in the context of a first breakpoint. Octet 2 - The PSD reduction for the sub-carrier indicated in octets 0 and 1. Octets 3-5 - Same, for a 2nd breakpoint. Octets 45-47 - Same, for a 3rd breakpoint. This architecture continues until octets 45-47, which are associated with a 16th breakpoint. Each subcarrier index is an unsigned number in the range 0 and (NSCus - 1). Each PSD reduction value is in the range 0 (0dBm/Hz) to 255 (-127.5dBm/Hz) with steps of 0.5dBm/Hz. Valid values are in the range 0 to 190 (0 to -95dBm/Hz). When the number of breakpoints is less than 16, all remaining octets are set to the value 0xff. Note that the content of this object should be correlated with the sub-carriers mask and with the RFI setup.

vdsl2SpectrumProfUpsPsdMaskSelection.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfUpsPsdMaskSelection
vdsl2SpectrumProfUpsPsdMaskSelection.description: This configuration parameter defines which upstream PSD mask is enabled. This parameter is used only for Annexes J and M of ITU T Recs G.992.3 and G.992.5. As only one selection parameter is defined in the MIB, the same selection value applies to all relevant modes enabled in the XTSE line configuration parameter. It ranges from 1 to 9 and selects the mask with the following definition This object is defaulted adlu-32/eu-32.

vdsl2SpectrumProfPmMode.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfPmMode
vdsl2SpectrumProfPmMode.description: Power management state Enabling. Defines the power states the ATU-C or ATU-R may autonomously transition to on this line. Options: 1. allowTransitionsToIdle (0) 2. allowTransitionsToLowPower (1) A bit with a '1' value means that the ATU is allowed to transit into the respective state and a '0' value means that the ATU is not allowed to transit into the respective state.

vdsl2SpectrumProfL0Time.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfL0Time
vdsl2SpectrumProfL0Time.description: This minimum time (in seconds) between an Exit from the L2 state and the next Entry into the L2 state. It ranges from 0 to 255 seconds. Unit: seconds

vdsl2SpectrumProfL2Time.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfL2Time
vdsl2SpectrumProfL2Time.description: This minimum time (in seconds) between an Entry into the L2 state and the first Power Trim in the L2 state and between two consecutive Power Trims in the L2 State. It ranges from 0 to 255 seconds. Unit: seconds

vdsl2SpectrumProfL2Atpr.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfL2Atpr
vdsl2SpectrumProfL2Atpr.description: The maximum aggregate transmit power reduction (in dB) that can be performed at transition of L0 to L2 state or through a single Power Trim in the L2 state. Unit: dB

vdsl2SpectrumProfL2Atprt.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfL2Atprt
vdsl2SpectrumProfL2Atprt.description: The total maximum aggregate transmit power reduction (in dB) that can be performed in an L2 state. This is the sum of all reductions of L2 Request (i.e., at transition of L0 to L2 state) and Power Trims. Unit: dB

vdsl2SpectrumProfModeSpecRowStatus.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfModeSpecRowStatus
vdsl2SpectrumProfModeSpecRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or to modify or delete an existing row in this table. A profile is activated by setting this object to 'active'. When 'active' is set, the system will validate the profile. Before a profile can be deleted or taken out of service (by setting this object to 'destroy' or 'outOfService'), it must be not referenced from all associated lines.

vdsl2SpectrumProfSubProfTable.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfSubProfTable
vdsl2SpectrumProfSubProfTable.description: The table vdsl2SpectrumProfSubProfTable extends the VDSL2 line configuration profile by profile parameters. The indexes of this table are vdsl2SpectrumProfName, vdsl2SpectrumProfXdslMode, and vdsl2SpectrumProfSubProfiles.

vdsl2SpectrumProfSubProfEntry.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfSubProfEntry
vdsl2SpectrumProfSubProfEntry.description: The table vdsl2SpectrumProfSubProfTable extends the VDSL2 line configuration profile by profile parameters. The indexes of this entry are vdsl2SpectrumProfName, vdsl2SpectrumProfXdslMode, and vdsl2SpectrumProfSubProfiles.

vdsl2SpectrumProfSubProfiles.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfSubProfiles
vdsl2SpectrumProfSubProfiles.description: This configuration parameter contains the G.993.2 profiles to be allowed by the near-end xTU on this line. This object is defaulted Profile17a.

vdsl2SpectrumProfSubProfilesWeight.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfSubProfilesWeight
vdsl2SpectrumProfSubProfilesWeight.description: This configuration parameter contains the G.993.2 profiles' weight to be allowed by the near-end xTU on this line. This object is defaulted priorityWeight1.

vdsl2SpectrumProfPsdClassMask.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfPsdClassMask
vdsl2SpectrumProfPsdClassMask.description: (CLASSMASK). In order to reduce the number of configuration possibilities, the limit Power Spectral Density masks (see LIMITMASK) are grouped in PSD mask classes. Each class is designed such that the PSD levels of each limit PSD mask of a specific class are equal in their respective passband above 276 kHz. This parameter is defined per VDSL2 Annex enabled in the xdsl2LConfProfXtuTransSysEna object. It selects a single PSD mask class per Annex that is activated at the VTU-O. This object is defaulted A998/B997M1c/C998.

vdsl2SpectrumProfPsdLimitMask.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfPsdLimitMask
vdsl2SpectrumProfPsdLimitMask.description: (LIMITMASK). This configuration parameter contains the G.993.2 limit PSD masks of the selected PSD mask class, enabled by the near-end xTU on this line for each class of profiles. This parameter is defined per VDSL2 Annex enabled in the xdsl2LConfProfXtuTransSysEna object. Through this parameter several limit PSD masks of the selected PSD mask class (xdsl2LConfProfClassMask) may be enabled. The enabling parameter is coded in a bitmap representation (0 if the associated mask is not allowed, 1 if it is allowed).This object is defaulted AnnexB998-M2x-B.

vdsl2SpectrumProfUs0PsdMask.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfUs0PsdMask
vdsl2SpectrumProfUs0PsdMask.description: This parameter contains the US0 PSD masks to be allowed by the near-end xTU on the line. This parameter is only defined for G.993.2 Annex A. It is represented as a bitmap (0 if not allowed and 1 if allowed) with the following definitions. This object is defaulted ADLU-32/EU-32.

vdsl2SpectrumProfUs0Disable.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfUs0Disable
vdsl2SpectrumProfUs0Disable.description: This configuration parameter indicates if the use of US0 is disabled for each limit PSD mask enabled in the LIMITMASK parameter. This object is defaulted Unused.

vdsl2SpectrumProfSubProfRowStatus.name: vdsl2SpectrumProfSubProfRowStatus
vdsl2SpectrumProfSubProfRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or to modify or delete an existing row in this table. A profile is activated by setting this object to 'active'. When 'active' is set, the system will validate the profile. Before a profile can be deleted or taken out of service (by setting this object to 'destroy' or 'outOfService'), it must be not referenced from all associated lines.

vdsl2DpboProfTable.name: vdsl2DpboProfTable
vdsl2DpboProfTable.description: The table vdsl2DpboProfTable contains VDSL2 DPBO configuration. The index of this table is vdsl2DpboProfName. A default profile with an index of 'DEFVAL' will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor-specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdsl2DpboProfEntry.name: vdsl2DpboProfEntry
vdsl2DpboProfEntry.description: The table vdsl2DpboProfTable contains VDSL2 DPBO configuration. The index of this entry is vdsl2DpboProfName. A default profile with an index of 'DEFVAL' will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor-specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdsl2DpboProfName.name: vdsl2DpboProfName
vdsl2DpboProfName.description: This object identifies a row in this table.

vdsl2DpboProfWkMdMask.name: vdsl2DpboProfWkMdMask
vdsl2DpboProfWkMdMask.description: This configuration parameter defines the current enabled DPBO working mode mask. DPBO working mode enabling:1-ADSL, 2-ADSL2+ 3-VDSL2. Options: 1. current enabled dpbo work mode:ADSL 2. current enabled dpbo work mode:ADSL2+ 3. current enabled dpbo work mode:ADSL,ADSL2+ 4. current enabled dpbo work mode:VDSL2 5. current enabled dpbo work mode:ADSL,VDSL2 6. current enabled dpbo work mode:ADSL2+,VDSL2 7. current enabled dpbo work mode:ADSL,ADSL2+,VDSL2

vdsl2DpboProfEpsd.name: vdsl2DpboProfEpsd
vdsl2DpboProfEpsd.description: This parameter defines the PSD mask that is assumed to be permitted at the exchange. This parameter shall use the same format as PSDMASKds.The maximum number of breakpoints for DPBOEPSD is 16. This is a string of 16 pairs of values in the following structure: Octets 0+1 - Index of 1st sub-carrier used in the context of a first breakpoint. Octet 2 - The PSD reduction for the sub-carrier indicated in octets 0 and 1. Octets 3-5 - Same, for a 2nd breakpoint. Octets 6-8 - Same, for a 3rd breakpoint. This architecture continues until octets 45-47, which are associated with a 16th breakpoint. Each subcarrier index is an unsigned number in the range 1 and NSCds. Each PSD reduction value is in the range 0 (0dBm/Hz) to 255 (-127.5dBm/Hz) with steps of 0.5dBm/Hz. Valid values are in the range 0 to 190 (0 to -95dBm/Hz). When the number of breakpoints is less than 16, all remaining octets are set to the value 0xff.

vdsl2DpboProfEsel.name: vdsl2DpboProfEsel
vdsl2DpboProfEsel.description: This configuration parameter defines the assumed electrical length of cables (E-side cables) connecting exchange based DSL services to a remote flexibility point (cabinet), that hosts the xTU-C that is subject to spectrally shaped downstream power back-off depending on this length. For this parameter the electrical length is defined as the loss (in dB) of an equivalent length of hypothetical cable at a reference frequency defined by the network operator or in spectrum management regulations. DPBOESEL shall be coded as an unsigned integer representing an electrical length from 0 dB (coded as 0) to 255.5 dB (coded as 511) in steps of 0.5 dB. All values in the range are valid.If DPBOESEL is set to zero, the DPBO in this section shall be disabled. Unit: 0.5dB

vdsl2DpboProfEscm.name: vdsl2DpboProfEscm
vdsl2DpboProfEscm.description: This configuration parameter defines a cable model in terms of three scalars DPBOESCMA, DPBOESCMB and DPBOESCMC that shall be used to describe the frequency dependent loss of E-side cables.Parameters DPBOESCMA, DPBOESCMB, DPBOESCMC shall be coded as unsigned integers representing a scalar value from -1 (coded as 0) to 1.5 (coded as 640) in step of 1/256. All values in the range are valid. Octets 0+1 DPBOESCMA Octets 2+3 DPBOESCMB Octets 4+5 DPBOESCMC

vdsl2DpboProfMus.name: vdsl2DpboProfMus
vdsl2DpboProfMus.description: DPBOMUS defines the assumed Minimum Usable receive Signal PSD (in dBm/Hz) for exchange based services, used to modify parameter DPBOFMAX defined below. It shall be coded as an unsigned integer representing a PSD level from 0 dBm/Hz (coded as 0) to -127.5 dBm/Hz (coded as 255) in steps of 0.5 dBm/Hz. All values in the range are valid. Unit: -0.5dBm/Hz

vdsl2DpboProfFmin.name: vdsl2DpboProfFmin
vdsl2DpboProfFmin.description: DPBOFMIN defines the minimum frequency from which the DPBO shall be applied. It shall be coded as a 16 bits unsigned integer representing a frequency in multiple of 4.3125 KHz. The range of valid values is from 0 kHz (coded as 0) to 8832 kHz (coded as 2048). Unit: 4.3125 KHz

vdsl2DpboProfFmax.name: vdsl2DpboProfFmax
vdsl2DpboProfFmax.description: DPBOFMAX defines the maximum frequency at which DPBO may be applied. It shall be coded as a 16 bits unsigned integer representing a frequency in multiple of 4.3125 KHz. The range of valid values is from 138 kHz (coded as 32) to 29997.75 kHz (coded as 6956). Unit: 4.3125 KHz

vdsl2DpboProfRowStatus.name: vdsl2DpboProfRowStatus
vdsl2DpboProfRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or to modify or delete an existing row in this table. A profile is activated by setting this object to 'active'. When 'active' is set, the system will validate the profile. Before a profile can be deleted or taken out of service (by setting this object to 'destroy' or 'outOfService'), it must be not referenced from all associated lines.

vdsl2DpboProfEselMin.name: vdsl2DpboProfEselMin
vdsl2DpboProfEselMin.description: DPBOESELMIN in dB is the minimum of all main cable losses for the KVz supplied when using the SOL model (expansion of a KVz and VDSL2 provision of additional KVz areas from this KVz using cross-cables to additional KVz), including the KVz at the MSAN site. This value must be adjustable as the minimum requirement via the SNMP interface in the configuration profile for each VDSL2 port, and is set individually for each MSAN site and usage. As an option, As an option, adjustment can be done for each MSAN or line card, thus taking effect for entire port groups. It is used only for determining the MUF. Unit: 0.5dB

vdsl2UpboProfTable.name: vdsl2UpboProfTable
vdsl2UpboProfTable.description: The table vdsl2UpboProfTable contains VDSL2 upbo configuration. The index of this table is vdsl2UpboProfName. A default profile with an index of 'DEFVAL' will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor-specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdsl2UpboProfEntry.name: vdsl2UpboProfEntry
vdsl2UpboProfEntry.description: The table vdsl2UpboProfTable contains VDSL2 upbo configuration . The index of this entry is vdsl2UpboProfName. A default profile with an index of 'DEFVAL' will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor-specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdsl2UpboProfName.name: vdsl2UpboProfName
vdsl2UpboProfName.description: This object identifies a row in this table.

vdsl2UpboProfPsdBand.name: vdsl2UpboProfPsdBand
vdsl2UpboProfPsdBand.description: This parameter defines the UPBO reference PSD used to compute the upstream power back-off for each upstream band. A UPBOPSD defined for each band shall consist of two parameters [a, b]. Parameter a shall be coded as an unsigned 12-bit number from 40 dBm/Hz (coded as 0) to 80.95 dBm/Hz (coded as 4095) in steps of 0.01 dBm/Hz; and b shall be coded as an unsigned 12 bit number from 0 (coded as 0) to 40.95 dBm/Hz (coded as 4095) in steps of 0.01 dBm/Hz. The UPBO reference PSD at the frequency f expressed in MHz shall be equal to '-a-b(SQRT(f))'. The set of parameter values a = 40 dBm/Hz, b = 0 dBm/Hz is a special configuration to disable UPBO in the respective upstream band. Octets 0+1 - a[0] Octets 2+3 - b[0] Octets 4+5 - a[1] Octets 6+7 - b[1] Octets 8+9 - a[2] Octets 10+11 - b[2] Octets 12+13 - a[3] Octets 14+15 - b[3] Octets 16+17 - a[4] Octets 18+19 - b[4]

vdsl2UpboProfKl.name: vdsl2UpboProfKl
vdsl2UpboProfKl.description: This parameter defines the electrical loop length expressed in dB at 1MHz, kl0, configured by the CO-MIB. The value shall be coded as an unsigned 16 bit number in the range 0 (coded as 0) to 128 dB (coded as 1280) in steps of 0.1 dB. Unit: 0.1 dB

vdsl2UpboProfKlf.name: vdsl2UpboProfKlf
vdsl2UpboProfKlf.description: This parameter is a flag that forces the VTU-R to use the electrical loop length of the CO-MIB (UPBOKL) to compute the UPBO. The value shall be forced if the flag is set to 1. Otherwise, the electrical loop length shall be autonomously selected by the VTU-O.

vdsl2UpboProfKlAuto.name: vdsl2UpboProfKlAuto
vdsl2UpboProfKlAuto.description: This parameter defines the mode in which kl0 is computed when Vdsl2UpboKlf is auto. The value is defined as below: 1-max(kl0CO,kl0CPE) 2-min(kl0CO,kl0CPE) 3-kl0CO 4-kl0CPE The default value is 3

vdsl2UpboProfRowStatus.name: vdsl2UpboProfRowStatus
vdsl2UpboProfRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or to modify or delete an existing row in this table. A profile is activated by setting this object to 'active'. When 'active' is set, the system will validate the profile. Before a profile can be deleted or taken out of service (by setting this object to 'destroy' or 'outOfService'), it must be not referenced from all associated lines.

vdsl2UpboProfBoostMode.name: vdsl2UpboProfBoostMode
vdsl2UpboProfBoostMode.description: This object indicates whether the equalized FEXT UPBO method is supported or not. Options: 1. disable(1) - The Equalized FEXT UPBO method is not supported 2. enable(2) - The Equalized FEXT UPBO method is supported

vdsl2UpboProfKl0RefBand.name: vdsl2UpboProfKl0RefBand
vdsl2UpboProfKl0RefBand.reference: This parameter defines the UPBO reference electrical length used to compute the upstream power back-off for each upstream band except US0, for the optional Equalized FEXT UPBO method. The value ranges from 1.8 to 63.5 dB in steps of 0.1 dB with special value 0.The special value 0 indicates optional Equalized FEXT UPBO method is not supported.
vdsl2UpboProfKl0RefBand.description: Octets 0+1 - length[1] Octets 2+3 - length[2] Octets 4+5 - length[3] Octets 6+7 - length[4]

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfTable.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfTable
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfTable.description: The table vdsl2NoiseMarginProfTable contains VDSL2 noise margin configuration. The index of this table is vdsl2NoiseMarginProfName. A default profile with an index of 'DEFVAL' will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor-specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfEntry.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfEntry
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfEntry.description: The table vdsl2NoiseMarginProfTable contains VDSL2 noise margin configuration. The index of this entry is vdsl2NoiseMarginProfName. A default profile with an index of 'DEFVAL' will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor-specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfName.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfName
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfName.description: This object identifies a row in this table.

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfTargetSnrmDs.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfTargetSnrmDs
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfTargetSnrmDs.description: The minimum Noise Margin the xTU-R receiver shall achieve, relative to the BER requirement for each of the downstream bearer channels, to successfully complete initialization. The target noise margin ranges from 0 to 310 units of 0.1 dB (Physical values are 0 to 31 dB). Unit: 0.1 dB

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfTargetSnrmUs.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfTargetSnrmUs
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfTargetSnrmUs.description: The minimum Noise Margin the xTU-C receiver shall achieve, relative to the BER requirement for each of the upstream bearer channels, to successfully complete initialization. The target noise margin ranges from 0 to 310 units of 0.1 dB (Physical values are 0 to 31 dB). Unit: 0.1 dB

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfMaxSnrmDs.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfMaxSnrmDs
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfMaxSnrmDs.description: The maximum Noise Margin the xTU-R receiver shall try to sustain. If the Noise Margin is above this level, the xTU-R shall request that the xTU-C reduce the xTU-C transmit power to get a noise margin below this limit (if this functionality is supported). The maximum noise margin ranges from 0 to 310 units of 0.1 dB (Physical values are 0 to 31 dB). A value of all 1's means that there is no maximum. Unit: 0.1 dB

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfMaxSnrmUs.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfMaxSnrmUs
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfMaxSnrmUs.description: The maximum Noise Margin the xTU-C receiver shall try to sustain. If the Noise Margin is above this level, the xTU-C shall request that the xTU-R reduce the xTU-R transmit power to get a noise margin below this limit (if this functionality is supported). The maximum noise margin ranges from 0 to 310 units of 0.1 dB (Physical values are 0 to 31 dB). A value of all 1's means that there is no maximum. Unit: 0.1 dB

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfMinSnrmDs.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfMinSnrmDs
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfMinSnrmDs.description: The minimum Noise Margin the xTU-R receiver shall tolerate. If the noise margin falls below this level, the xTU-R shall request that the xTU-C increase the xTU-C transmit power. If an increase to xTU-C transmit power is not possible, a loss-of-margin (LOM) defect occurs, the xTU-R shall fail and attempt to reinitialize and the NMS shall be notified. The minimum noise margin ranges from 0 to 310 units of 0.1 dB (Physical values are 0 to 31 dB). A value of 0 means that there is no minimum. Unit: 0.1 dB

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfMinSnrmUs.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfMinSnrmUs
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfMinSnrmUs.description: The minimum Noise Margin the xTU-C receiver shall tolerate. If the noise margin falls below this level, the xTU-C shall request that the xTU-R increase the xTU-R transmit power. If an increase of xTU-R transmit power is not possible, a loss-of-margin (LOM) defect occurs, the xTU-C shall fail and attempt to re-initialize and the NMS shall be notified. The minimum noise margin ranges from 0 to 310 units of 0.1 dB (Physical values are 0 to 31 dB). A value of 0 means that there is no minimum. Unit: 0.1 dB

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaUsNrmDs.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaUsNrmDs
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaUsNrmDs.description: The Downstream Up-Shift Noise Margin value, to be used when Vdsl2LineConfRaModeDs is set to DynamicRa. If the downstream noise margin is above this value and stays above it for more than the time specified by the Vdsl2ServProfRaUsTimeDs, the xTU-R shall attempt to increase the downstream net data rate. The Downstream Up-shift Noise Margin ranges from 0 to 310 units of 0.1 dB (Physical values are 0 to 31 dB). Unit: 0.1 dB

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaUsNrmUs.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaUsNrmUs
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaUsNrmUs.description: The Upstream Up-Shift Noise Margin value, to be used when Vdsl2LineConfRaModeUs is set to DynamicRa. If the upstream noise margin is above this value and stays above it for more than the time specified by the Vdsl2LineConfRaUsTimeUs, the xTU-C shall attempt to increase the upstream net data rate. The Upstream Up-shift Noise Margin ranges from 0 to 310 units of 0.1 dB (Physical values are 0 to 31 dB). Unit: 0.1 dB

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaUsTimeDs.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaUsTimeDs
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaUsTimeDs.description: The Downstream Up-Shift Time Interval, to be used when Vdsl2LineConfRaModeDs is set to DynamicRa. The interval of time that the downstream noise margin should stay above the Downstream Up-shift Noise Margin before the xTU-R shall attempt to increase the downstream net data rate. Unit: seconds

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaUsTimeUs.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaUsTimeUs
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaUsTimeUs.description: The Upstream Up-Shift Time Interval, to be used when Vdsl2LineConfRaModeUs is set to DynamicRa. The interval of time the upstream noise margin should stay above the Upstream Up-shift Noise Margin before the xTU-C shall attempt to increase the upstream net data rate. Unit: seconds

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaDsNrmsDs.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaDsNrmsDs
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaDsNrmsDs.description: The Downstream Down-Shift Noise Margin value, to be used when Vdsl2LineConfRaModeDs is set to DynamicRa. If the downstream noise margin is below this value and stays below that for more than the time specified by the Vdsl2LineConfRaDsTimeDs, the xTU-R shall attempt to decrease the downstream net data rate. The Downstream Down-shift Noise Margin ranges from 0 to 310 units of 0.1 dB (Physical values are 0 to 31 dB). Unit: 0.1 dB

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaDsNrmsUs.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaDsNrmsUs
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaDsNrmsUs.description: The Upstream Downshift Noise Margin value, to be used when Vdsl2LineConfRaModeUs is set to DynamicRa. If the upstream noise margin is below this value and stays below that for more than the time specified by the Vdsl2LineConfRaDsTimeUs, the xTU-C shall attempt to decrease the upstream net data rate. The Upstream Down-shift Noise Margin ranges from 0 to 310 units of 0.1 dB (Physical values are 0 to 31 dB). Unit: 0.1 dB

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaDsTimeDs.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaDsTimeDs
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaDsTimeDs.description: The Downstream Downshift Time Interval, to be used when Vdsl2LineConfRaModeDs is set to DynamicRa. The interval of time the downstream noise margin should stay below the Downstream Down-shift Noise Margin before the xTU-R shall attempt to decrease the downstream net data rate. Unit: seconds

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaDsTimeUs.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaDsTimeUs
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRaDsTimeUs.description: The Upstream Down-Shift Time Interval, to be used when Vdsl2LineConfRaModeUs is set to DynamicRa. The interval of time the upstream noise margin should stay below the Upstream Down-shift Noise Margin before the xTU-C shall attempt to decrease the upstream net data rate. Unit: seconds

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfDsThresholdDs.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfDsThresholdDs
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfDsThresholdDs.description: Data Rate Threshold Downshift for downstream direction. A 'Down-shift rate change' event is triggered when the actual downstream data rate is below the data rate at the last entry into Showtime, by more than the threshold. The parameter is coded in bit/s. Unit: bits/second

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfUsThresholdDs.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfUsThresholdDs
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfUsThresholdDs.description: Data Rate Threshold Up shift for downstream direction. An 'Up-shift rate change' event is triggered when the actual downstream data rate exceeds, by more than the threshold, the data rate at the last entry into Showtime. The parameter is coded in bit/s. Unit: bits/second

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfDsThresholdUs.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfDsThresholdUs
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfDsThresholdUs.description: Data Rate Threshold Downshift for upstream direction. A 'Down-shift rate change' event is triggered when the actual upstream data rate is below the data rate at the last entry into Showtime, by more than the threshold. The parameter is coded in bit/s. Unit: bits/second

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfUsThresholdUs.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfUsThresholdUs
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfUsThresholdUs.description: Data Rate Threshold Up shift for upstream direction. An 'Up-shift rate change' event is triggered when the actual upstream data rate exceeds, by more than the threshold, the data rate at the last entry into Showtime. The parameter is coded in bit/s. Unit: bits/second

vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRowStatus.name: vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRowStatus
vdsl2NoiseMarginProfRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or to modify or delete an existing row in this table. A profile is activated by setting this object to 'active'. When 'active' is set, the system will validate the profile. Before a profile can be deleted or taken out of service (by setting this object to 'destroy' or 'outOfService'), it must be not referenced from all associated lines.

vdsl2DelayInpProfTable.name: vdsl2DelayInpProfTable
vdsl2DelayInpProfTable.description: The table vdsl2DelayInpProfTable contains VDSL2 delay inp configuration. The index of this table is vdsl2DelayInpProfName. A default profile with an index of 'DEFVAL' will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor-specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdsl2DelayInpProfEntry.name: vdsl2DelayInpProfEntry
vdsl2DelayInpProfEntry.description: The table vdsl2DelayInpProfTable contains VDSL2 delay inp configuration. The index of this entry is vdsl2DelayInpProfName. A default profile with an index of 'DEFVAL' will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor-specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdsl2DelayInpProfName.name: vdsl2DelayInpProfName
vdsl2DelayInpProfName.description: This object identifies a row in this table.

vdsl2DelayInpProfForceINP.name: vdsl2DelayInpProfForceINP
vdsl2DelayInpProfForceINP.description: This parameter indicates that the framer settings of the bearer shall be selected such that the impulse noise protection computed according to the formula specified in the relevant Recommendation is greater or equal to the minimal impulse noise protection requirement. This flag shall have the same value for all the bearers of one line in the same direction.

vdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MaxDelayDs.name: vdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MaxDelayDs
vdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MaxDelayDs.description: If retransmission is not used in downstream direction,this parameter is maximum interleave delay on downstream direction. The maximum one-way interleaving delay introduced by the PMS-TC on Downstream direction. The XTUs shall choose the S (factor) and D (depth) values such that the actual one-way interleaving delay (Vdsl2ChanStatusActDelay) is as close as possible to, but less than or equal to, Vdsl2ChanConfMaxDelayDs. The delay is coded in ms, with the value 0 indicating no delay bound is being imposed. Unit: milliseconds

vdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MaxDelayUs.name: vdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MaxDelayUs
vdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MaxDelayUs.description: If retransmission is not used in upstream direction. The maximum one-way interleaving delay introduced by the PMS-TC on Upstream direction. The XTUs shall choose the S (factor) and D (depth) values such that the actual one-way interleaving delay (Vdsl2ChanStatusActDelay) is as close as possible to, but less than or equal to, Vdsl2ChanConfMaxDelayUs. The delay is coded in ms, with the value 0 indicating no delay bound is being imposed. Unit: milliseconds

vdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MinProtectionDs.name: vdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MinProtectionDs
vdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MinProtectionDs.description: If retransmission is not used in downstream direction,this parameter is minimum impulse noise protection for the bearer channel on downstream direction. The minimum impulse noise protection for the bearer channel, expressed in symbols. The parameter can take the following values: noProtection (i.e., INP not required), halfSymbol (i.e., INP length is 1/2 symbol) and 1-16 symbols in steps of 1 symbol. Unit: symbols

vdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MinProtectionUs.name: vdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MinProtectionUs
vdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MinProtectionUs.description: If retransmission is not used in upstream direction,this parameter is minimum impulse noise protection for the bearer channel on upstream direction. The minimum impulse noise protection for the bearer channel, expressed in symbols. The parameter can take the following values: noProtection (i.e., INP not required), halfSymbol (i.e., INP length is 1/2 symbol) and 1-16 symbols in steps of 1 symbol. Unit: symbols

vdsl2DelayInpProfCh2MaxDelayDs.name: vdsl2DelayInpProfCh2MaxDelayDs
vdsl2DelayInpProfCh2MaxDelayDs.description: Maximum Interleave Delay on Downstream direction. The maximum one-way interleaving delay introduced by the PMS-TC on Downstream direction. The XTUs shall choose the S (factor) and D (depth) values such that the actual one-way interleaving delay (Vdsl2ChanStatusActDelay) is as close as possible to, but less than or equal to, Vdsl2ChanConfMaxDelayDs. The delay is coded in ms, with the value 0 indicating no delay bound is being imposed. Unit: milliseconds

vdsl2DelayInpProfCh2MaxDelayUs.name: vdsl2DelayInpProfCh2MaxDelayUs
vdsl2DelayInpProfCh2MaxDelayUs.description: Maximum Interleave Delay on Upstream direction. The maximum one-way interleaving delay introduced by the PMS-TC on Upstream direction. The XTUs shall choose the S (factor) and D (depth) values such that the actual one-way interleaving delay (Vdsl2ChanStatusActDelay) is as close as possible to, but less than or equal to, Vdsl2ChanConfMaxDelayUs. The delay is coded in ms, with the value 0 indicating no delay bound is being imposed. Unit: milliseconds

vdsl2DelayInpProfCh2MinProtectionDs.name: vdsl2DelayInpProfCh2MinProtectionDs
vdsl2DelayInpProfCh2MinProtectionDs.description: Minimum Impulse Noise Protection on Downstream direction. The minimum impulse noise protection for the bearer channel, expressed in symbols. The parameter can take the following values: noProtection (i.e., INP not required), halfSymbol (i.e., INP length is 1/2 symbol) and 1-16 symbols in steps of 1 symbol. Unit: symbols

vdsl2DelayInpProfCh2MinProtectionUs.name: vdsl2DelayInpProfCh2MinProtectionUs
vdsl2DelayInpProfCh2MinProtectionUs.description: Minimum Impulse Noise Protection on Upstream direction. The minimum impulse noise protection for the bearer channel, expressed in symbols. The parameter can take the following values: noProtection (i.e., INP not required), halfSymbol (i.e., INP length is 1/2 symbol) and 1-16 symbols in steps of 1 symbol. Unit: symbols

hwvdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MinInpShineRtxDs.name: hwvdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MinInpShineRtxDs
hwvdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MinInpShineRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum impulse noise protection against SHINE for the bearer channel if it is transported over DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 4.3125 kHz. The impulse noise protection is expressed in DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 4.3125 kHz and can take any integer value from 0 to 63, inclusive. Unit: symbols

hwvdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MinInp8ReinRtxDs.name: hwvdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MinInp8ReinRtxDs
hwvdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MinInp8ReinRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum impulse noise protection against REIN for the bearer channel if it is transported over DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 8.625 kHz. The impulse noise protection is expressed in DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 8.625 kHz and can take any integer value from 0 to 13, inclusive.

hwvdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MinInp8ReinRtxUs.name: hwvdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MinInp8ReinRtxUs
hwvdsl2DelayInpProfCh1MinInp8ReinRtxUs.description: If retransmission is used in upstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum impulse noise protection against REIN for the bearer channel if it is transported over DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 8.625 kHz. The impulse noise protection is expressed in DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 8.625 kHz and can take any integer value from 0 to 13, inclusive.

hwvdsl2DelayInpProfCh1IatReinRtxDs.name: hwvdsl2DelayInpProfCh1IatReinRtxDs
hwvdsl2DelayInpProfCh1IatReinRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the inter-arrival time that shall be assumed for REIN protection. Options: 1. frequency100Hz(0) - an inter-arrival time derived from a REIN at 100 Hz 2. frequency120Hz(1) - an inter-arrival time derived from a REIN at 120 Hz

hwvdsl2DelayInpProfCh1IatReinRtxUs.name: hwvdsl2DelayInpProfCh1IatReinRtxUs
hwvdsl2DelayInpProfCh1IatReinRtxUs.description: If retransmission is used in upstream direction, this parameter specifies the inter-arrival time that shall be assumed for REIN protection. Options: 1. frequency100Hz(0) - an inter-arrival time derived from a REIN at 100 Hz 2. frequency120Hz(1) - an inter-arrival time derived from a REIN at 120 Hz

vdsl2ChConfProfileTable.name: vdsl2ChConfProfileTable
vdsl2ChConfProfileTable.description: The table vdsl2ChConfProfileTable contains VDSL2 channel profile configuration. The index of this table is vdsl2ChConfProfProfileName. A default profile with an index of 'DEFVAL' will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor-specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdsl2ChConfProfileEntry.name: vdsl2ChConfProfileEntry
vdsl2ChConfProfileEntry.description: The table vdsl2ChConfProfileTable contains VDSL2 channel profile configuration. The index of this entry is vdsl2ChConfProfProfileName. A default profile with an index of 'DEFVAL' will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor-specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdsl2ChConfProfProfileName.name: vdsl2ChConfProfProfileName
vdsl2ChConfProfProfileName.description: This object identifies a row in this table.

vdsl2ChConfProfMinDataRateDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinDataRateDs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinDataRateDs.description: If retransmission is not used in downstream direction,this parameter specifics minimum data rate for the bearer channel on downstream direction. The rate is coded in steps of 1000 bit/s. Unit: bits/second

vdsl2ChConfProfMinDataRateUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinDataRateUs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinDataRateUs.description: If retransmission is not used in upstream direction,this parameter specifics minimum data rate for the bearer channel on upstream direction. The rate is coded in steps of 1000 bit/s Unit: bits/second

vdsl2ChConfProfMinResDataRateDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinResDataRateDs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinResDataRateDs.description: Minimum Reserved Data Rate on Downstream direction. The minimum reserved net data rate for the bearer channel, coded in bit/s. This parameter is used only if the Rate Adaptation Mode in the direction of the bearer channel (i.e., Vdsl2LineConfRaModeDs) is set to DynamicRa. Unit: bits/second

vdsl2ChConfProfMinResDataRateUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinResDataRateUs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinResDataRateUs.description: Minimum Reserved Data Rate on Upstream direction. The minimum reserved net data rate for the bearer channel, coded in bit/s. This parameter is used only if the Rate Adaptation Mode in the direction of the bearer channel (i.e., Vdsl2LineConfRaModeUs) is set to DynamicRa. Unit: bits/second

vdsl2ChConfProfMaxDataRateDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMaxDataRateDs
vdsl2ChConfProfMaxDataRateDs.description: If retransmission is not used in downstream direction,this parameter specifics maximum data rate for the bearer channel on downstream direction. The rate is coded in steps of 1000 bit/s. Unit: bits/second

vdsl2ChConfProfMaxDataRateUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMaxDataRateUs
vdsl2ChConfProfMaxDataRateUs.description: If retransmission is not used in upstream direction,this parameter specifics maximum data rate for the bearer channel on upstream direction. The rate is coded in steps of 1000 bit/s. Unit: bits/second

vdsl2ChConfProfMinDataRateLowPwrDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinDataRateLowPwrDs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinDataRateLowPwrDs.description: Minimum Data Rate in Low Power state on Downstream direction. The minimum net data rate for the bearer channel, coded in bit/s, during the low power state (L1 in G.992.2, L2 in G.992.3). Unit: bits/second

vdsl2ChConfProfMinDataRateLowPwrUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinDataRateLowPwrUs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinDataRateLowPwrUs.description: Minimum Data Rate in Low Power state on Upstream direction. The minimum net data rate for the bearer channel, coded in bit/s, during the low power state (L1 in G.992.2, L2 in G.992.3). Unit: bits/second

vdsl2ChConfProfMaxDelayDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMaxDelayDs
vdsl2ChConfProfMaxDelayDs.description: If retransmission is not used in downstream direction,this parameter is maximum interleave delay on downstream direction. The maximum one-way interleaving delay introduced by the PMS-TC on Downstream direction. The XTUs shall choose the S (factor) and D (depth) values such that the actual one-way interleaving delay (Vdsl2ChanStatusActDelay) is as close as possible to, but less than or equal to, Vdsl2ChanConfMaxDelayDs. The delay is coded in ms, with the value 0 indicating no delay bound is being imposed. Unit: milliseconds

vdsl2ChConfProfMaxDelayUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMaxDelayUs
vdsl2ChConfProfMaxDelayUs.description: If retransmission is not used in upstream direction,this parameter is maximum interleave delay on upstream direction. The maximum one-way interleaving delay introduced by the PMS-TC on Upstream direction. The XTUs shall choose the S (factor) and D (depth) values such that the actual one-way interleaving delay (Vdsl2ChanStatusActDelay) is as close as possible to, but less than or equal to, Vdsl2ChanConfMaxDelayUs. The delay is coded in ms, with the value 0 indicating no delay bound is being imposed. Unit: milliseconds

vdsl2ChConfProfMinProtectionDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinProtectionDs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinProtectionDs.description: If retransmission is not used in downstream direction,this parameter is minimum impulse noise protection for the bearer channel on downstream direction. The minimum impulse noise protection for the bearer channel, expressed in symbols. The parameter can take the following values: noProtection (i.e., INP not required), halfSymbol (i.e., INP length is 1/2 symbol) and 1-16 symbols in steps of 1 symbol. Unit: symbols

vdsl2ChConfProfMinProtectionUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinProtectionUs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinProtectionUs.description: If retransmission is not used in upstream direction,this parameter is minimum impulse noise protection for the bearer channel on upstream direction. The minimum impulse noise protection for the bearer channel, expressed in symbols. The parameter can take the following values: noProtection (i.e., INP not required), halfSymbol (i.e., INP length is 1/2 symbol) and 1-16 symbols in steps of 1 symbol. Unit: symbols

vdsl2ChConfProfMaxBerDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMaxBerDs
vdsl2ChConfProfMaxBerDs.description: Maximum Bit Error Ratio on Downstream direction. The maximum bit error ratio for the bearer channel. The parameter can take the following values (for 1E-3, 1E-5 or 1E-7). Options: 1. eminus3 (1) - 1E-3 2. eminus5 (2) - 1E-5 3. eminus7 (3) - 1E-7

vdsl2ChConfProfMaxBerUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMaxBerUs
vdsl2ChConfProfMaxBerUs.description: Maximum Bit Error Ratio on Upstream direction. The maximum bit error ratio for the bearer channel. The parameter can take the following values (for 1E-3, 1E-5 or 1E-7). Options: 1. eminus3 (1) - 1E-3 2. eminus5 (2) - 1E-5 3. eminus7 (3) - 1E-7

vdsl2ChConfProfUsDataRateDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfUsDataRateDs
vdsl2ChConfProfUsDataRateDs.description: If retransmission is not used in downstream direction,this parameter is data rate threshold upshift for downstream direction. An 'Up-shift rate change' event is triggered when the actual downstream data rate exceeds, by more than the threshold, the data rate at the last entry into Showtime. The parameter is coded in bit/s. Unit: bits/second

vdsl2ChConfProfDsDataRateDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfDsDataRateDs
vdsl2ChConfProfDsDataRateDs.description: If retransmission is not used in downstream direction,this parameter is data rate threshold downshift for downstream direction. A 'Down-shift rate change' event is triggered when the actual downstream data rate is below the data rate at the last entry into Showtime, by more than the threshold. The parameter is coded in bit/s. Unit: bits/second

vdsl2ChConfProfUsDataRateUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfUsDataRateUs
vdsl2ChConfProfUsDataRateUs.description: If retransmission is not used in upstream direction,this parameter is data rate threshold up shift for upstream direction. An 'Up-shift rate change' event is triggered when the actual upstream data rate exceeds, by more than the threshold, the data rate at the last entry into Showtime. The parameter is coded in bit/s. Unit: bits/second

vdsl2ChConfProfDsDataRateUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfDsDataRateUs
vdsl2ChConfProfDsDataRateUs.description: If retransmission is not used in upstream direction,this parameter is data rate threshold downshift for upstream direction. A 'Down-shift rate change' event is triggered when the actual upstream data rate is below the data rate at the last entry into Showtime, by more than the threshold. The parameter is coded in bit/s. Unit: bits/second

vdsl2ChConfProfImaEnabled.name: vdsl2ChConfProfImaEnabled
vdsl2ChConfProfImaEnabled.description: IMA Mode Enable. The parameter enables the IMA operation mode in the ATM Data Path. Relevant only if the channel is of ATM Data Path. When in 'enable' state, the ATM data path should comply with the requirements for IMA transmission.

vdsl2ChConfProfDataPathMode.name: vdsl2ChConfProfDataPathMode
vdsl2ChConfProfDataPathMode.description: The channel data path mode. Options: 1. atm(1) - ATM 2. ptm(2) - PTM 3. both(3) - ATM and PTM Huawei defined.

vdsl2ChConfProfRowStatus.name: vdsl2ChConfProfRowStatus
vdsl2ChConfProfRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or to modify or delete an existing row in this table. A profile is activated by setting this object to 'active'. When 'active' is set, the system will validate the profile. Before a profile can be deleted or taken out of service (by setting this object to 'destroy' or 'outOfService'), it must be not referenced from all associated templates.

vdsl2ChConfProfPhyRcontrolDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfPhyRcontrolDs
vdsl2ChConfProfPhyRcontrolDs.description: To enable or disable the retransmission function.

vdsl2ChConfProfPhyRcontrolUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfPhyRcontrolUs
vdsl2ChConfProfPhyRcontrolUs.description: To enable or disable the retransmission function.

vdsl2ChConfProfInpMaxDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfInpMaxDs
vdsl2ChConfProfInpMaxDs.description: Maximum Impulse Noise Protection on downstream direction.

vdsl2ChConfProfInpMaxUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfInpMaxUs
vdsl2ChConfProfInpMaxUs.description: Maximum Impulse Noise Protection on upstream direction.

vdsl2ChConfProfMinRtxRatioDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinRtxRatioDs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinRtxRatioDs.description: This object is used to config the minimum retransmission band width parameter downstream.

vdsl2ChConfProfMinRtxRatioUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinRtxRatioUs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinRtxRatioUs.description: This object is used to config the minimum retransmission band width parameter upstream.

vdsl2ChConfProfMinRSoverheadDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinRSoverheadDs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinRSoverheadDs.description: This object is used to config the minimum RSoverhead parameter downstream..

vdsl2ChConfProfMinRSoverheadUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinRSoverheadUs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinRSoverheadUs.description: This object is used to config the minimum RSoverhead parameter upstream..

vdsl2ChConfProfErasureDecoding.name: vdsl2ChConfProfErasureDecoding
vdsl2ChConfProfErasureDecoding.description: To enable or disable the erasure decoding of a channel. Options: 1. enable(1) 2. disable(2)

vdsl2ChConfProfMinSosBrDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinSosBrDs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinSosBrDs.description: This parameter specifies the minimum net data rate required for a valid SOS request in the downstream direction. The valid range of values is from 0 to 524280Kbps in steps of 8Kbps. Unit: 8Kbps

vdsl2ChConfProfMinSosBrUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinSosBrUs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinSosBrUs.description: This parameter specifies the minimum net data rate required for a valid SOS request in the upstream direction.The valid range of values is from 0 to 524280Kbps in steps of 8Kbps. Unit: 8Kbps

vdsl2ChConfProfMinEtrRtxDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinEtrRtxDs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinEtrRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum expected throughput for the bearer channel.The values range in steps of 1000 bit/s.

vdsl2ChConfProfMinEtrRtxUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinEtrRtxUs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinEtrRtxUs.description: If retransmission is used in upstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum expected throughput for the bearer channel.The values range in steps of 1000 bit/s.

vdsl2ChConfProfMaxEtrRtxDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMaxEtrRtxDs
vdsl2ChConfProfMaxEtrRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the maximum expected throughput for the bearer channel.The values range in steps of 1000 bit/s.

vdsl2ChConfProfMaxEtrRtxUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMaxEtrRtxUs
vdsl2ChConfProfMaxEtrRtxUs.description: If retransmission is used in upstream direction, this parameter specifies the maximum expected throughput for the bearer channel.The values range in steps of 1000 bit/s.

vdsl2ChConfProfMaxNdrRtxDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMaxNdrRtxDs
vdsl2ChConfProfMaxNdrRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the maximum net data rate for the bearer channel. The values range in steps of 1000 bit/s.

vdsl2ChConfProfMaxNdrRtxUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMaxNdrRtxUs
vdsl2ChConfProfMaxNdrRtxUs.description: If retransmission is used in upstream direction, this parameter specifies the maximum net data rate for the bearer channel.The values range in steps of 1000 bit/s.

vdsl2ChConfProfMaxDelayRtxDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMaxDelayRtxDs
vdsl2ChConfProfMaxDelayRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the maximum for the instantaneous delay due to the effect of retransmission only (see G.998.4 for detailed specification). The delay ranges from 1 to 63 ms by steps of 1 ms. Unit: milliseconds

vdsl2ChConfProfMaxDelayRtxUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMaxDelayRtxUs
vdsl2ChConfProfMaxDelayRtxUs.description: If retransmission is used in upstream direction, this parameter specifies the maximum for the instantaneous delay due to the effect of retransmission only (see G.998.4 for detailed specification). The delay ranges from 1 to 63 ms by steps of 1 ms. Unit: milliseconds

vdsl2ChConfProfMinDelayRtxDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinDelayRtxDs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinDelayRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum for the instantaneous delay due to the effect of retransmission only (see G.998.4 for detailed specification). The delay ranges from 0 to 63 ms by steps of 1 ms. Unit: milliseconds

vdsl2ChConfProfMinDelayRtxUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinDelayRtxUs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinDelayRtxUs.description: If retransmission is used in upstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum for the instantaneous delay due to the effect of retransmission only (see G.998.4 for detailed specification). The delay ranges from 0 to 63 ms by steps of 1 ms. Unit: milliseconds

vdsl2ChConfProfMinInpShineRtxDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinInpShineRtxDs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinInpShineRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum impulse noise protection against SHINE for the bearer channel if it is transported over DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 4.3125 kHz. The impulse noise protection is expressed in DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 4.3125 kHz and can take any integer value from 0 to 63, inclusive. Unit: symbols

vdsl2ChConfProfMinInpShineRtxUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinInpShineRtxUs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinInpShineRtxUs.description: If retransmission is used in upstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum impulse noise protection against SHINE for the bearer channel if it is transported over DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 4.3125 kHz. The impulse noise protection is expressed in DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 4.3125 kHz and can take any integer value from 0 to 63, inclusive. Unit: symbols

vdsl2ChConfProfMinInp8ShineRtxDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinInp8ShineRtxDs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinInp8ShineRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum impulse noise protection against SHINE for the bearer channel if it is transported over DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 8.625 kHz. The impulse noise protection is expressed in DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 8.625 kHz and can take any integer value from 0 to 127, inclusive. Unit: symbols

vdsl2ChConfProfMinInp8ShineRtxUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinInp8ShineRtxUs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinInp8ShineRtxUs.description: If retransmission is used in upstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum impulse noise protection against SHINE for the bearer channel if it is transported over DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 8.625 kHz. The impulse noise protection is expressed in DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 8.625 kHz and can take any integer value from 0 to 127, inclusive. Unit: symbols

vdsl2ChConfProfShineRatioRtxDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfShineRatioRtxDs
vdsl2ChConfProfShineRatioRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the SHINE ratio (detailed definition see G.998.4). The values range from 0 to 0.100 in increments of 0.001.

vdsl2ChConfProfShineRatioRtxUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfShineRatioRtxUs
vdsl2ChConfProfShineRatioRtxUs.description: If retransmission is used in upstream direction, this parameter specifies the SHINE ratio (detailed definition see G.998.4). The values range from 0 to 0.100 in increments of 0.001.

vdsl2ChConfProfMinInpReinRtxDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinInpReinRtxDs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinInpReinRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum impulse noise protection against REIN for the bearer channel if it is transported over DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 4.3125 kHz. The impulse noise protection is expressed in DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 4.3125 kHz and can take any integer value from 0 to 7, inclusive.

vdsl2ChConfProfMinInpReinRtxUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinInpReinRtxUs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinInpReinRtxUs.description: If retransmission is used in upstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum impulse noise protection against REIN for the bearer channel if it is transported over DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 4.3125 kHz. The impulse noise protection is expressed in DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 4.3125 kHz and can take any integer value from 0 to 7, inclusive.

vdsl2ChConfProfMinInp8ReinRtxDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinInp8ReinRtxDs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinInp8ReinRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum impulse noise protection against REIN for the bearer channel if it is transported over DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 8.625 kHz. The impulse noise protection is expressed in DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 8.625 kHz and can take any integer value from 0 to 13, inclusive.

vdsl2ChConfProfMinInp8ReinRtxUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfMinInp8ReinRtxUs
vdsl2ChConfProfMinInp8ReinRtxUs.description: If retransmission is used in upstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum impulse noise protection against REIN for the bearer channel if it is transported over DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 8.625 kHz. The impulse noise protection is expressed in DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 8.625 kHz and can take any integer value from 0 to 13, inclusive.

vdsl2ChConfProfIatReinRtxDs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfIatReinRtxDs
vdsl2ChConfProfIatReinRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the inter-arrival time that shall be assumed for REIN protection. Options: 1. frequency100Hz(0) - an inter-arrival time derived from a REIN at 100 Hz 2. frequency120Hz(1) - an inter-arrival time derived from a REIN at 120 Hz

vdsl2ChConfProfIatReinRtxUs.name: vdsl2ChConfProfIatReinRtxUs
vdsl2ChConfProfIatReinRtxUs.description: If retransmission is used in upstream direction, this parameter specifies the inter-arrival time that shall be assumed for REIN protection. Options: 1. frequency100Hz(0) - an inter-arrival time derived from a REIN at 100 Hz 2. frequency120Hz(1) - an inter-arrival time derived from a REIN at 120 Hz

vdsl2ChConfProfInitPolicy.name: vdsl2ChConfProfInitPolicy
vdsl2ChConfProfInitPolicy.description: This parameter indicates which policy shall be applied to determine the transceiver configuration parameters at initialization. The valid values for CIPOLICY are 0,1 and 2. Those policies are defined in the respective recommendations. Options: 1. policy0 (1) - Policy 0 according to the applicable standard 2. policy1 (2) - Policy 1 according to the applicable standard 3. policy2 (3) - Policy 2 according to the applicable standard

vdsl2LineAlarmConfTemplateTable.name: vdsl2LineAlarmConfTemplateTable
vdsl2LineAlarmConfTemplateTable.description: The table vdsl2LineAlarmConfTemplateTable contains VDSL2 line alarm configuration template. The index of this table is vdsl2LAlarmConfTempTemplateName. A default template with an index of 'DEFVAL' will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdsl2LineAlarmConfTemplateEntry.name: vdsl2LineAlarmConfTemplateEntry
vdsl2LineAlarmConfTemplateEntry.description: The table vdsl2LineAlarmConfTemplateTable contains VDSL2 line alarm configuration template. The index of this entry is vdsl2LAlarmConfTempTemplateName. A default template with an index of 'DEFVAL' will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdsl2LAlarmConfTempTemplateName.name: vdsl2LAlarmConfTempTemplateName
vdsl2LAlarmConfTempTemplateName.description: This object identifies a row in this table.

vdsl2LAlarmConfTempLineProfile.name: vdsl2LAlarmConfTempLineProfile
vdsl2LAlarmConfTempLineProfile.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the VDSL2 Line Thresholds Configuration Profile Table (vdsl2LineAlarmConfProfileTable) that applies to this VDSL2 line.

vdsl2LAlarmConfTempChan1ConfProfile.name: vdsl2LAlarmConfTempChan1ConfProfile
vdsl2LAlarmConfTempChan1ConfProfile.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the VDSL2 Channel Thresholds Configuration Profile Table (vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileTable) that applies for VDSL2 bearer channel #1. The channel profile name specified here must match the name of an existing row in the vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileTable table.

vdsl2LAlarmConfTempChan2ConfProfile.name: vdsl2LAlarmConfTempChan2ConfProfile
vdsl2LAlarmConfTempChan2ConfProfile.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the VDSL2 Channel Thresholds Configuration Profile Table (vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileTable) that applies for VDSL2 bearer channel #2. The channel profile name specified here must match the name of an existing row in the vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileTable table. If the channel is unused, then the object is set to a zero length string.

vdsl2LAlarmConfTempChan3ConfProfile.name: vdsl2LAlarmConfTempChan3ConfProfile
vdsl2LAlarmConfTempChan3ConfProfile.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the VDSL2 Channel Thresholds Configuration Profile Table (vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileTable) that applies for VDSL2 bearer channel #3. The channel profile name specified here must match the name of an existing row in the vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileTable table. This object may be set to a non-zero length string only if vdsl2LAlarmConfTempChan2ConfProfile contains a non-zero length string.

vdsl2LAlarmConfTempChan4ConfProfile.name: vdsl2LAlarmConfTempChan4ConfProfile
vdsl2LAlarmConfTempChan4ConfProfile.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the VDSL2 Channel Thresholds Configuration Profile Table (vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileTable) that applies for VDSL2 bearer channel #4. The channel profile name specified here must match the name of an existing row in the vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileTable table. This object may be set to a non-zero length string only if vdsl2LAlarmConfTempChan3ConfProfile contains a non-zero length string.

vdsl2LAlarmConfTempRowStatus.name: vdsl2LAlarmConfTempRowStatus
vdsl2LAlarmConfTempRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or to modify or delete an existing row in this table. A profile is activated by setting this object to 'active'. When 'active' is set, the system will validate the profile. Before a profile can be deleted or taken out of service (by setting this object to 'destroy' or 'outOfService'), it must be not referenced from all associated lines.

vdsl2LineAlarmConfProfileTable.name: vdsl2LineAlarmConfProfileTable
vdsl2LineAlarmConfProfileTable.description: The table vdsl2LineAlarmConfProfileTable contains VDSL2 line PM thresholds profiles. The index of this table is vdsl2LineAlarmConfProfileName. A default profile with an index of 'DEFVAL' will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdsl2LineAlarmConfProfileEntry.name: vdsl2LineAlarmConfProfileEntry
vdsl2LineAlarmConfProfileEntry.description: The table vdsl2LineAlarmConfProfileTable contains VDSL2 line PM thresholds profiles. The index of this entry is vdsl2LineAlarmConfProfileName. A default profile with an index of 'DEFVAL' will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdsl2LineAlarmConfProfileName.name: vdsl2LineAlarmConfProfileName
vdsl2LineAlarmConfProfileName.description: This object identifies a row in this table.

vdsl2LineAlarmConfProfileXtucThresh15Min.name: vdsl2LineAlarmConfProfileXtucThresh15MinFecs
vdsl2LineAlarmConfProfileXtucThresh15Min.description: A threshold for the vdsl2PMLCurr15MFecs counter, when vdsl2PMLCurrUnit is XTUC {1}. The value 0 means that no threshold is specified for the associated counter. Unit: seconds

Options: 1. enable(1) - The alarm switch that the port frequently retrain times in 15 minutes reach the threshold is enabled 2. disable(2) - The alarm switch that the port frequently retrain times in 15 minutes reach the threshold is disabled

hwvdsl2LineAlarmConfProfilePSConfigAbnor.name: hwvdsl2LineAlarmConfProfilePSConfigAbnormalAlarmSwitch
