vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileTable.name: vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileTable
vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileTable.description: The table vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileTable contains VDSL2 channel PM thresholds profiles. The index of this table is vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileName. A default profile with an index of 'DEFVAL' will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor-specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileEntry.name: vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileEntry
vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileEntry.description: The table vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileTable contains VDSL2 channel PM thresholds profiles. The index of this entry is vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileName. A default profile with an index of 'DEFVAL' will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor-specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileName.name: vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileName
vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileName.description: This object identifies a row in this table.

vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileXtucThresh15MinCo.name: vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileXtucThresh15MinCodingViolations
vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileXtucThresh15MinCo.description: A threshold for the vdsl2PMChCurr15MCodingViolations counter, when vdsl2PMChCurrUnit is XTUC {1}. The value 0 means that no threshold is specified for the associated counter.

vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileXtucThresh15MinCo.name: vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileXtucThresh15MinCorrected
vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileXtucThresh15MinCo.description: A threshold for the vdsl2PMChCurr15MCorrectedBlocks counter, when vdsl2PMChCurrUnit is XTUC {1}. The value 0 means that no threshold is specified for the associated counter.

vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileXturThresh15MinCo.name: vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileXturThresh15MinCodingViolations
vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileXturThresh15MinCo.description: A threshold for the vdsl2PMChCurr15MCodingViolations counter, when vdsl2PMChCurrUnit is XTUR {2}. The value 0 means that no threshold is specified for the associated counter.

vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileXturThresh15MinCo.name: vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileXturThresh15MinCorrected
vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileXturThresh15MinCo.description: A threshold for the vdsl2PMChCurr15MCorrectedBlocks counter, when vdsl2PMChCurrUnit is XTUR {2}. The value 0 means that no threshold is specified for the associated counter.

vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileMonitoringRateDs.name: vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileMonitoringRateDs
vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileMonitoringRateDs.description: The channel monitoring rate downstream. Huawei defined. When the value you set is larger than the value of the rate downstream defined in the channel profile, it will not be successful. The value 0 means that no threshold is specified for the associated counter. Unit: bits/second

vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileMonitoringRateUs.name: vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileMonitoringRateUs
vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileMonitoringRateUs.description: The channel monitoring rate upstream. Huawei defined. When the value you set is larger than the value of the rate upstream defined in the channel profile, it will not be successful. The value 0 means that no threshold is specified for the associated counter. Unit: bits/second

vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileRowStatus.name: vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileRowStatus
vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfileRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or to modify or delete an existing row in this table. A profile is activated by setting this object to 'active'. When 'active' is set, the system will validate the profile. Before a profile can be deleted or taken out of service (by setting this object to 'destroy' or 'outOfService'), it must be not referenced from all associated templates.

vdsl2PMLineCurrTable.name: vdsl2PMLineCurrTable
vdsl2PMLineCurrTable.description: The table vdsl2PMLineCurrTable contains current Performance Monitoring results of VDSL2 line. The indexes of this table are an interface index where the interface has an ifType of vdsl2(251) and the termination unit.

vdsl2PMLineCurrEntry.name: vdsl2PMLineCurrEntry
vdsl2PMLineCurrEntry.description: The table vdsl2PMLineCurrTable contains current Performance Monitoring results of VDSL2 line. The indexes of this entry are an interface index where the interface has an ifType of vdsl2(251) and the termination unit.

vdsl2PMLCurrUnit.name: vdsl2PMLCurrUnit
vdsl2PMLCurrUnit.description: The termination unit XTUC{1} or XTUR{2}.

vdsl2PMLCurr15MTimeElapsed.name: vdsl2PMLCurr15MTimeElapsed
vdsl2PMLCurr15MTimeElapsed.description: Total elapsed seconds in this interval. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLCurr15MFecs.name: vdsl2PMLCurr15MFecs
vdsl2PMLCurr15MFecs.description: Count of seconds during this interval that there was at least one FEC correction event for one or more bearer channels in this line. This parameter is inhibited during UAS or SES. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLCurr15MEs.name: vdsl2PMLCurr15MEs
vdsl2PMLCurr15MEs.description: Count of seconds during this interval that there was: xTU-C: CRC-8 >= 1 for one or more bearer channels OR LOS >= 1 OR SEF >=1 OR LPR >= 1 xTU-R: FEBE >= 1 for one or more bearer channels OR LOS-FE >=1 OR RDI >=1 OR LPR-FE >=1 . This parameter is inhibited during UAS. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLCurr15MSes.name: vdsl2PMLCurr15MSes
vdsl2PMLCurr15MSes.description: Count of seconds during this interval that there was: xTU-C: If G.998.4 is supported and retransmission is enabled in the near-end received direction, a SES is declared if during a 1-second interval, there is one or more severe loss of error-free throughput (seftr) defect in the near-end received direction. Or else, an SES is declared if, during a 1 second interval, there are 18 or more CRC 8 anomalies in one or more of the received bearer channels, or one or more LOS defects, or one or more SEF defects, or one or more LPR defects. xTU-R: If G.998.4 is supported and retransmission is enabled in the far-end received direction, a SES-LFE is declared if during a 1-second interval, there is one or more severe loss of error-free throughput (seftr) defect in the far-end received direction. Or else, an SES is declared if, during a 1 second interval, there are 18 or more FEBE anomalies in one or more of the transmitted bearer channels, or one or more far end LOS defects, or one or more RDI defects, or one or more LPR FE defects. This parameter is inhibited during UAS. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLCurr15MLoss.name: vdsl2PMLCurr15MLoss
vdsl2PMLCurr15MLoss.description: Count of seconds during this interval that there was LOS (or LOS-FE for xTU-R). Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLCurr15MUas.name: vdsl2PMLCurr15MUas
vdsl2PMLCurr15MUas.description: Count of seconds in Unavailability State during this interval. Unavailability begins at the onset of 10 contiguous severely-errored seconds, and ends at the onset of 10 contiguous seconds with no severely-errored seconds. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLCurr1DayTimeElapsed.name: vdsl2PMLCurr1DayTimeElapsed
vdsl2PMLCurr1DayTimeElapsed.description: Total elapsed seconds in this interval. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLCurr1DayFecs.name: vdsl2PMLCurr1DayFecs
vdsl2PMLCurr1DayFecs.description: Count of seconds during this interval that there was at least one FEC correction event for one or more bearer channels in this line. This parameter is inhibited during UAS or SES. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLCurr1DayEs.name: vdsl2PMLCurr1DayEs
vdsl2PMLCurr1DayEs.description: Count of seconds during this interval that there was: xTU-C: CRC-8 >= 1 for one or more bearer channels OR LOS >= 1 OR SEF >= 1 OR LPR >= 1 xTU-R: FEBE >= 1 for one or more bearer channels OR LOS-FE >= 1 OR RDI >= 1 OR LPR-FE >= 1. This parameter is inhibited during UAS. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLCurr1DaySes.name: vdsl2PMLCurr1DaySes
vdsl2PMLCurr1DaySes.description: Count of seconds during this interval that there was: xTU-C: (CRC-8 summed over all bearer channels) >= 18 OR LOS >= 1 OR SEF >= 1 OR LPR >= 1 xTU-R: (FEBE summed over all bearer channels) >= 18 OR LOS-FE >= 1 OR RDI >= 1 OR LPR-FE >= 1 This parameter is inhibited during UAS. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLCurr1DayLoss.name: vdsl2PMLCurr1DayLoss
vdsl2PMLCurr1DayLoss.description: Count of seconds during this interval that there was LOS (or LOS-FE for xTU-R). Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLCurr1DayUas.name: vdsl2PMLCurr1DayUas
vdsl2PMLCurr1DayUas.description: Count of seconds in Unavailability State during this interval. Unavailability begins at the onset of 10 contiguous severely -errored seconds, and ends at the onset of 10 contiguous seconds with no severely-errored seconds. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLEverBeforeFecs.name: vdsl2PMLEverBeforeFecs
vdsl2PMLEverBeforeFecs.description: Count of seconds since agent reset that there was at least one FEC correction event for one or more bearer channels in this line. This parameter is inhibited during UAS or SES. Huawei defined. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLEverBeforeEs.name: vdsl2PMLEverBeforeEs
vdsl2PMLEverBeforeEs.description: Count of seconds since agent reset that there was: xTU-C: CRC-8 >= 1 for one or more bearer channels OR LOS >= 1 OR SEF >= 1 OR LPR >= 1 xTU-R: FEBE >= 1 for one or more bearer channels OR LOS-FE >= 1 OR RDI >= 1 OR LPR-FE >= 1. This parameter is inhibited during UAS. Huawei defined. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLEverBeforeSes.name: vdsl2PMLEverBeforeSes
vdsl2PMLEverBeforeSes.description: Count of seconds since agent reset that there was: xTU-C: (CRC-8 summed over all bearer channels) >= 18 OR LOS >= 1 OR SEF >= 1 OR LPR >= 1 xTU-R: (FEBE summed over all bearer channels) >= 18 OR LOS-FE >= 1 OR RDI >= 1 OR LPR-FE >= 1 This parameter is inhibited during UAS. Huawei defined. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLEverBeforeLoss.name: vdsl2PMLEverBeforeLoss
vdsl2PMLEverBeforeLoss.description: Count of seconds since agent reset that there was LOS (or LOS-FE for xTU-R). Huawei defined. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLEverBeforeUas.name: vdsl2PMLEverBeforeUas
vdsl2PMLEverBeforeUas.description: Count of seconds in Unavailability State since agent reset. Unavailability begins at the onset of 10 contiguous severely -errored seconds, and ends at the onset of 10 contiguous seconds with no severely-errored seconds. Huawei defined. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLCurr15MLofs.name: vdsl2PMLCurr15MLofs
vdsl2PMLCurr15MLofs.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was Loss of Framing. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLCurr15MLols.name: vdsl2PMLCurr15MLols
vdsl2PMLCurr15MLols.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was Loss of Link. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLCurr15MLops.name: vdsl2PMLCurr15MLops
vdsl2PMLCurr15MLops.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was Loss of Power. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLCurr1DayLofs.name: vdsl2PMLCurr1DayLofs
vdsl2PMLCurr1DayLofs.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was Loss of Framing during the current day. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLCurr1DayLols.name: vdsl2PMLCurr1DayLols
vdsl2PMLCurr1DayLols.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was Loss of Link during the current day. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLCurr1DayLops.name: vdsl2PMLCurr1DayLops
vdsl2PMLCurr1DayLops.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was Loss of Power during the current day. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLEverBeforeLofs.name: vdsl2PMLEverBeforeLofs
vdsl2PMLEverBeforeLofs.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was Loss of Framing since agent reset. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLEverBeforeLols.name: vdsl2PMLEverBeforeLols
vdsl2PMLEverBeforeLols.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was Loss of Link since agent reset. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLEverBeforeLops.name: vdsl2PMLEverBeforeLops
vdsl2PMLEverBeforeLops.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was Loss of Power since agent reset. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLCurr15MSosSuccess.name: vdsl2PMLCurr15MSosSuccess
vdsl2PMLCurr15MSosSuccess.description: Count of the total number of successful SOS procedures initiated in the current 15 minute. Unit: times

vdsl2PMLCurr1DaySosSuccess.name: vdsl2PMLCurr1DaySosSuccess
vdsl2PMLCurr1DaySosSuccess.description: Count of the total number of successful SOS procedures initiated during the current day. Unit: times

vdsl2PMLEverBeforeSosSuccess.name: vdsl2PMLEverBeforeSosSuccess
vdsl2PMLEverBeforeSosSuccess.description: Count of the total number of successful SOS procedures initiated since agent reset. Unit: times

vdsl2PMLCurr15MInmainpeq.name: vdsl2PMLCurr15MInmainpeq
vdsl2PMLCurr15MInmainpeq.description: This parameter is a count of the INMAINPEQi anomalies occurring on the line during current 15 minutes.

vdsl2PMLCurr15MInmame.name: vdsl2PMLCurr15MInmame
vdsl2PMLCurr15MInmame.description: This parameter is a count of the INMAME anomalies occurring on the line during current 15 minutes.

vdsl2PMLCurr15MInmaiat.name: vdsl2PMLCurr15MInmaiat
vdsl2PMLCurr15MInmaiat.description: This parameter is a count of the INMAIATi anomalies occurring on the line during current 15 minutes.

vdsl2PMLCurr1DayInmainpeq.name: vdsl2PMLCurr1DayInmainpeq
vdsl2PMLCurr1DayInmainpeq.description: This parameter is a count of the INMAINPEQi anomalies occurring on the line during current 1 day.

vdsl2PMLCurr1DayInmame.name: vdsl2PMLCurr1DayInmame
vdsl2PMLCurr1DayInmame.description: This parameter is a count of the INMAME anomalies occurring on the line during current 1 day.

vdsl2PMLCurr1DayInmaiat.name: vdsl2PMLCurr1DayInmaiat
vdsl2PMLCurr1DayInmaiat.description: This parameter is a count of the INMAIATi anomalies occurring on the line during current 1 day.

vdsl2PMLEverBeforeInmainpeq.name: vdsl2PMLEverBeforeInmainpeq
vdsl2PMLEverBeforeInmainpeq.description: This parameter is a count of the INMAINPEQi anomalies occurring on the line ever before.

vdsl2PMLEverBeforeInmame.name: vdsl2PMLEverBeforeInmame
vdsl2PMLEverBeforeInmame.description: This parameter is a count of the INMAME anomalies occurring on the line ever before.

vdsl2PMLEverBeforeInmaiat.name: vdsl2PMLEverBeforeInmaiat
vdsl2PMLEverBeforeInmaiat.description: This parameter is a count of the INMAIATi anomalies occurring on the line ever before.

vdsl2PMLineCurr15MStartTime.name: vdsl2PMLineCurr15MStartTime
vdsl2PMLineCurr15MStartTime.description: Start time of the current 15-minute performance statistics.

vdsl2PMLineCurr1DayStartTime.name: vdsl2PMLineCurr1DayStartTime
vdsl2PMLineCurr1DayStartTime.description: Start time of the current 1-day performance statistics.

vdsl2PMLCurr15MLeftrs.name: vdsl2PMLCurr15MLeftrs
vdsl2PMLCurr15MLeftrs.description: If retransmission is used in a given transmit direction, this parameter is a count of the seconds with a near-end leftr defect present observed over the 15 minutes accumulation period.

vdsl2PMLCurr15MEfb.name: vdsl2PMLCurr15MEfb
vdsl2PMLCurr15MEfb.description: If retransmission is used in a given transmit direction, this parameter is a count of the number of error-free bits observed over the 15 minutes accumulation period.

vdsl2PMLCurr15MMinEftr.name: vdsl2PMLCurr15MMinEftr
vdsl2PMLCurr15MMinEftr.description: If retransmission is used in a given transmit direction, this parameter reports the minimum of the EFTR(Error-free throughput rate) observed over the 15 minutes accumulation period.

vdsl2PMLCurr1DayLeftrs.name: vdsl2PMLCurr1DayLeftrs
vdsl2PMLCurr1DayLeftrs.description: If retransmission is used in a given transmit direction, this parameter is a count of the seconds with a near-end leftr defect present observed over the 24 hours accumulation period.

vdsl2PMLCurr1DayEfb.name: vdsl2PMLCurr1DayEfb
vdsl2PMLCurr1DayEfb.description: If retransmission is used in a given transmit direction, this parameter is a count of the number of error-free bits observed over the 24 hours accumulation period.

vdsl2PMLCurr1DayMinEftr.name: vdsl2PMLCurr1DayMinEftr
vdsl2PMLCurr1DayMinEftr.description: If retransmission is used in a given transmit direction, this parameter reports the minimum of the EFTR(Error-free throughput rate) observed over the 24 hours accumulation period.

vdsl2PMLEverBeforeLeftrs.name: vdsl2PMLEverBeforeLeftrs
vdsl2PMLEverBeforeLeftrs.description: If retransmission is used in a given transmit direction, this parameter is a count of the seconds with a near-end leftr defect present observed ever before.

vdsl2PMLEverBeforeEfb.name: vdsl2PMLEverBeforeEfb
vdsl2PMLEverBeforeEfb.description: If retransmission is used in a given transmit direction, this parameter is a count of the number of error-free bits observed ever before.

vdsl2PMLEverBeforeMinEftr.name: vdsl2PMLEverBeforeMinEftr
vdsl2PMLEverBeforeMinEftr.description: If retransmission is used in a given transmit direction, this parameter reports the minimum of the EFTR(Error-free throughput rate) observed ever before.

vdsl2PMLHist15MEs.name: vdsl2PMLHist15MEs
vdsl2PMLHist15MEs.description: Count of seconds during this interval that there was: xTU-C: CRC-8 >= 1 for one or more bearer channels OR LOS >= 1 OR SEF >= 1 OR LPR >= 1 xTU-R: FEBE >= 1 for one or more bearer channels OR LOS-FE >= 1 OR RDI >= 1 OR LPR-FE >= 1. This parameter is inhibited during UAS. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLHist15MSes.description: Count of seconds during this interval that there was: xTU-C: (CRC-8 summed over all bearer channels) >= 18 OR LOS >= 1 OR SEF >= 1 OR LPR >= 1 xTU-R: (FEBE summed over all bearer channels) >= 18 OR LOS-FE >= 1 OR RDI >= 1 OR LPR-FE >= 1. This parameter is inhibited during UAS. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLHist15MUas.description: Count of seconds in Unavailability State during this interval. Unavailability begins at the onset of 10 contiguous severely -errored seconds, and ends at the onset of 10 contiguous seconds with no severely-errored seconds. Unit: seconds

vdsl2PMLHist15MValidInterval.name: vdsl2PMLHist15MValidInterval
vdsl2PMLHist15MValidInterval.description: This variable indicates if the data for this interval is valid.

vdsl2DpboEselGlobalConfigSwitch.name: vdsl2DpboEselGlobalConfigSwitch
vdsl2DpboEselGlobalConfigSwitch.description: Enable/Disable VDSL port DPBOESEL shall Feature. This object is defaulted disabled(2). Options: 1. enabled(1) - enabled the switch 2. disabled(2) - disabled the switch

vdsl2DpboEselGlobalConfigValue.name: vdsl2DpboEselGlobalConfigValue
vdsl2DpboEselGlobalConfigValue.description: This configuration parameter defines the assumed electrical length of cables (E-side cables) connecting exchange based DSL services to a remote flexibility point (cabinet), that hosts the xTU-C that is subject to spectrally shaped downstream power back-off depending on this length. For this parameter the electrical length is defined as the loss (in dB) of an equivalent length of hypothetical cable at a reference frequency defined by the network operator or in spectrum management regulations. DPBOESEL shall be coded as an unsigned integer representing an electrical length from 0 dB (coded as 0) to 255.5 dB (coded as 511) in steps of 0.5 dB. All values in the range are valid.If DPBOESEL is set to zero, the DPBO in this section shall be disabled. This object is defaulted 84. Unit: 0.5dB

vdsl2ProfileAutoNegotiationSwitch.name: vdsl2ProfileAutoNegotiationSwitch

vdsl2MaximumInterleavedDepth.name: vdsl2MaximumInterleavedDepth
vdsl2MaximumInterleavedDepth.description: Set the VDSL2 maximum interleaved depth function. Default values:maxInterleavedDepth511(2). Options: 1. maxInterleavedDepth64(1) - it means the interleaving depth up to 64 can be selected 2. maxInterleavedDepth511(2) - it means the interleaving depth up to 512 can be selected

hwvdsl2AutoDeleteProfUnusedProfType.description: The profile type of deleting unused VDSL profile. Options: 1. vdsl2LineConfTemplate(1) - VDSL2 line template 2. vdsl2LineConfProf(2) - VDSL2 line profile 3. vdsl2ChConfProfile(3) - VDSL2 channel profile 4. vdsl2LineAlarmConfTemplate(4) - VDSL2 alarm template 5. vdsl2LineAlarmConfProfile(5) - VDSL2 alarm profile 6. vdsl2ChAlarmConfProfile(6) - VDSL2 channel alarm profile 7. vdsl2ServProf(7) - VDSL2 service profile 8. vdsl2SpectrumProf(8) - VDSL2 spectrum profile 9. vdsl2DpboProf(9) - VDSL2 dpbo profile 10. vdsl2UpboProf(10) - VDSL2 upbo profile 11. vdsl2NoiseMarginProf(11) - VDSL2 noise-margin profile 12. vdsl2DelayInpProf(12) - VDSL2 inp-delay profile 13. vopDataRateConfProf(13) - XDSL data rate profile 14. vopLineSpectrumConfProf(14) - XDSL line spectrum profile 15. vopUPBOConfProf(15) - XDSL upbo profile 16. vopDPBOConfProf(16) - XDSL dpbo profile 17. vopRFIConfProf(17) - XDSL rfi profile 18. vopSNRMarginConfProf(18) - XDSL noise-margin profile 19. vopINPDelayConfProf(19) - XDSL inp-delay profile 20. vopVirtualNoiseConfProf(20) - XDSL virtual noise profile 21. vopModeSpecificPSDConfProf(21) - XDSL PSD profile
